<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06174213 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06174213 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  CELEBRITY; PET; BASEBALL; CLUB; OFFICIAL; CINCINNATI; CANCER; VICTIM  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Schottzie, the St. Bernard who belongs to Cincinnati Reds owner Marge Schott,has bone cancer and will undergo chemotherapy and radiation treatments nextweek.;    Veterinarians said the 9-year-old, 150-pound female dog has advancedosteosarcoma, a bone cancer common in large breeds, in the right front leg.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  ST. BERNARD SCHOTTZIE HAS CANCER  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     &quot;People who have pets know what this is like,&quot; Schott said. &quot;She is specialto me.&quot;;    The dog has made frequent appearances with Schott at Reds homegames, although a younger St. Bernard is reported to have filled inoccasionally in the past couple of seasons.;    &quot;Treatment will not make thecancer go away,&quot; said Dr. Cheryl Harris, who will administer the chemotherapy.&quot;Hopefully, she will have a good quality of life and we will make her feelbetter.&quot;  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910622  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4E  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  128  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday June 22, 199100174213,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>